					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13141045#post-4809752</guid>
				<title>+1</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13141045/scp-5522#post-4809752</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 02 Nov 2020 14:26:43 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>ADudeCalledLeo</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>6881864</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Speedrunning is already extremely weird in a normal game context, putting it in a real-life context ups the ante a lot. <em>And I love it.</em></p> <p>I was a bit confused by the last bit until I realized that the shock collar is technically a tool, and that the shocks would interfere with the speedrun. Therefore, it was a Tool Assisted Speedrun. Smart.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
